---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'aetna-international', text: 'Aetna International', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'geoblue', text: 'GeoBlue', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'US Expat Insurance', href: '/best/us-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-aetna-international' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'US Network', aetna: 'CVS/Aetna network', cigna: 'Cigna US network', geoblue: 'BCBS network' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage Quality', aetna: 'Excellent', cigna: 'Very Good', geoblue: 'Excellent' },
  { feature: 'Global Network', aetna: '1M+ providers', cigna: '1.5M+ providers', geoblue: '500K+ providers' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing (US)', aetna: 'Excellent', cigna: 'Good', geoblue: 'Excellent' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing (Global)', aetna: 'Good', cigna: 'Excellent', geoblue: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Plan Flexibility', aetna: 'Moderate', cigna: 'High', geoblue: 'Low' },
  { feature: 'Mobile App', aetna: 'Good', cigna: 'Excellent', geoblue: 'Basic' },
  { feature: 'Best Region', aetna: 'Americas', cigna: 'Worldwide', geoblue: 'US-focused' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35 (w/ US)', aetna: '$280-380/mo', cigna: '$300-400/mo', geoblue: '$250-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 50 (w/ US)', aetna: '$450-550/mo', cigna: '$480-580/mo', geoblue: '$400-500/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40 (w/ US)', aetna: '$550-700/mo', cigna: '$580-750/mo', geoblue: '$480-620/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4 (w/ US)', aetna: '$800-1000/mo', cigna: '$850-1050/mo', geoblue: '$720-900/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna vs Cigna vs GeoBlue: Best Insurance for US Expats 2026"
  description="Compare the top 3 insurers for Americans abroad: Aetna International, Cigna Global, and GeoBlue. US network access, pricing, and which is best for your situation."
  headline="Aetna vs Cigna vs GeoBlue: Which Is Best for US Expats?"
  subheadline="The three insurers Americans abroad should consider. All offer strong US coverage—here's how to choose."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best US Network</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">GeoBlue</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Blue Cross Blue Shield network access. Best direct billing in the US. More limited globally.</p>
      <a href="/go/geoblue" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get GeoBlue Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Largest global network plus solid US coverage. Most flexible plans. Higher price.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Integration</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">CVS Health integration. Strong Americas coverage. Good balance of US and global.</p>
      <a href="/go/aetna-international" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    All three insurers understand American healthcare expectations. The choice depends on whether you prioritize US network access (GeoBlue), global flexibility (Cigna), or integrated US healthcare services (Aetna).
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="aetna-international">Aetna International</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">CVS Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Americas Focus</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Integrated Care</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Aetna International is part of CVS Health, giving them unique integration with US healthcare services. If you value pharmacy benefits, MinuteClinic access, and a familiar American healthcare experience, Aetna delivers.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>CVS Health integration (pharmacy, MinuteClinic)</li>
    <li>Strong Aetna network in the US</li>
    <li>Good Americas coverage (US, Canada, Latin America)</li>
    <li>Familiar to Americans with domestic Aetna</li>
    <li>Solid telemedicine options</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Global network not as large as Cigna</li>
    <li>Less plan flexibility than competitors</li>
    <li>Stronger in Americas than Asia/Europe</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Americans who want CVS integration, those focused on the Americas, people who value familiar US-style healthcare.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Largest Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Most Flexible</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global offers the most comprehensive worldwide coverage of the three, with a massive 1.5M+ provider network. While their US coverage is good, their real strength is being equally capable anywhere in the world.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Largest global network (1.5M+ providers)</li>
    <li>Industry-leading mobile app</li>
    <li>Highly customizable modular plans</li>
    <li>Strong in every region worldwide</li>
    <li>Excellent direct billing globally</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>US network not as integrated as GeoBlue/Aetna</li>
    <li>Highest premiums of the three</li>
    <li>May be overkill if you're US-focused</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Americans living globally who need equal coverage everywhere, frequent travelers, those who may relocate between countries.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="geoblue">GeoBlue</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">BCBS Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best US Access</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lower Price</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    GeoBlue is backed by Blue Cross Blue Shield, giving them access to the most recognized healthcare network in America. If seamless US healthcare access is your top priority, GeoBlue is hard to beat.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Blue Cross Blue Shield network access</li>
    <li>Best direct billing in the US</li>
    <li>Lower premiums than Cigna/Aetna</li>
    <li>Simple, straightforward plans</li>
    <li>Strong brand recognition in US</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smaller global network (500K vs 1.5M)</li>
    <li>Less direct billing outside US</li>
    <li>Fewer plan customization options</li>
    <li>Mobile app less sophisticated</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Americans who return to the US frequently, those prioritizing US healthcare access, budget-conscious expats who want BCBS backing.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/geoblue" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get GeoBlue Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/geoblue" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Aetna, Cigna, and GeoBlue based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    All prices include US coverage, which significantly impacts premiums. Here's what to expect for comprehensive plans:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive plans including US coverage. Actual quotes vary by individual factors.
  </p>

  <h3>Why US Coverage Costs More</h3>

  <p>
    American healthcare is the most expensive in the world. Adding US coverage typically increases premiums by 30-50% compared to worldwide-excluding-US plans. All three insurers price US coverage similarly because the underlying costs are the same.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you won't be in the US often, consider whether you really need full US coverage or if emergency-only US coverage would suffice at a lower price.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose GeoBlue if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Return to the US frequently for healthcare</li>
        <li>Want Blue Cross Blue Shield network access</li>
        <li>Prioritize US coverage over global coverage</li>
        <li>Want lower premiums than Cigna/Aetna</li>
        <li>Prefer simple, straightforward plans</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Need strong coverage in multiple countries</li>
        <li>Want the largest global provider network</li>
        <li>May relocate between countries</li>
        <li>Value a great mobile app experience</li>
        <li>Want maximum plan flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Aetna International if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want CVS Health integration (pharmacy, clinics)</li>
        <li>Live in the Americas (US, Canada, Latin America)</li>
        <li>Have existing Aetna coverage you like</li>
        <li>Value integrated healthcare services</li>
        <li>Want strong telemedicine options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Which has the best US network?</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue, thanks to Blue Cross Blue Shield access. BCBS is the most widely accepted insurance network in America. Aetna is also excellent through CVS Health. Cigna's US network is good but not as comprehensive.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use these plans when visiting the US?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, all three cover US visits when you include US coverage. This is essential for American expats who return home regularly. Without US coverage, you'd pay out of pocket for any US care.
  </p>

  <h3>Which is cheapest?</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue typically has the lowest premiums, followed by Aetna, then Cigna. However, GeoBlue's smaller global network means you may face more out-of-network situations outside the US.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I rarely visit the US?</h3>
  <p>
    If you're in the US less than a few weeks per year, Cigna Global's worldwide-excluding-US plan might be a better value. You'd save 30-40% on premiums and still have emergency coverage if you visit.
  </p>

  <h3>Do these work with US Medicare?</h3>
  <p>
    These are private international plans, separate from Medicare. If you're Medicare-eligible, these can complement Medicare when abroad (since Medicare doesn't cover overseas care) but operate independently.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
